        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 25 at 6:55PM EDT until September 25 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>SVRGSP

The National Weather Service in Greenville-Spartanburg has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Rutherford County in western North Carolina...
Southwestern Cleveland County in the Piedmont of North Carolina...
Northern Spartanburg County in Upstate South Carolina...
Northwestern Cherokee County in Upstate South Carolina...

* Until 800 PM EDT.

* At 654 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 11 miles north of
Spartanburg, or 4 miles north of Boiling Springs SC, moving east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

* Locations impacted include...
Gaffney, Boiling Springs SC, Boiling Springs NC, Inman, Blacksburg,
Mayo, Chesnee, Campobello, Lattimore, and Mooresboro.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please report damaging winds, hail, or flooding to the National
Weather Service by calling toll free, 1, 800, 2 6 7, 8 1 0 1, or by
posting on our Facebook page, or post it to X using hashtag nwsgsp.
Your message should describe the event and the specific location
where it occurred.</instruction>
